2.2. Applications studied
‚Ä¢ High Performance Linpack benchmark [2] (HPL for short) is a classic application for solving a system of linear
equations and is widely used to measure supercomputer performance. It was our prime object of study for this
paper.
‚Ä¢ Netperfmeter [3] is a benchmark for measuring the speed of TCP/UDP communication. It was used to Ô¨Ånd the
accuracy of performance measurements of network models.
‚Ä¢ Gromacs [4] is a molecular dynamics simulation package. This is the one of ‚Äúproduction‚Äù applications running
on the GenX systems.
The following tools were used for building and running the applications.
‚Ä¢
