Compiler ‚Äì Intel Composer XE 2011 SP1 6.233 (icc version 12.1.0)
MPI library ‚Äì MPICH 1.4.1p1.
Applications: HPL 2.0, Netperfmeter 1.1.7, Gromacs 4.5.4 (double precision, MPI support).
Operating system of real and simulated clusters: Debian GNU/Linux 6.0.3 x86 64.

2.3. Metrics studied
The Ô¨Årst thing to perform within a full system simulation is to ensure a correct operation of the software on the
simulated hardware conÔ¨Åguration; that is, will it work and yield sane results. For this a functional model is enough as
it ensures the correctness of the software algorithms. The next step is to Ô¨Ånd the performance.
We use FLOPS (Ô¨Çoating point operations per second) as a measure of how fast an application is performing on
the whole cluster. To characterize performance per a single core another value will be used, namely CPI ‚Äì average
processor clocks ticks required to retire one machine instruction. Having the core CPI one can easily get the cluster
FLOPS with the formula
